## What is EC2?
EC2 is a virtual server in AWS.
 
### 🔹 What I Covered
• What is EC2  
• Instance types (t2.micro, t3.micro)  
• AMI (Amazon Machine Image)  
• Key pairs for SSH access  
• Security Groups configuration  
• Public vs Private EC2 deployment  
 
### 📝 Key Points
• EC2 is a virtual machine running in AWS.  
• Instance type defines CPU, RAM, and performance.  
• AMI is a template used to launch instances.  
• Key Pair is required to securely connect via SSH.  
• Security Group acts as a stateful firewall.  
• Public EC2 has internet access; Private EC2 does not.
 
